@component history-store
@intent EG-side v1 distillation of the DB P2 HistoryStore backend abstraction shipped by main upstream commit `a28150e` (separate file `history-store.cjs`, ~580 lines, factored out of `server.cjs`). Owns per-channel append-only event persistence behind a single contract surface; three operational modes form a strict opt-in chain — **mode A (`jsonl` — JSONL-only, default + P1 floor) · mode B (`dual` — JsonlStore + SqliteStore dual-write + one-shot backfill, transitional) · mode C (`sqlite` — SQLite primary, terminal opt-in, JSONL regenerated on demand via `exportJsonl()`)**. `SqliteStore` and `HistoryStoreMux` are **dormant by default** — a fresh install starts in mode A and never loads a SQLite driver; mode-B/C is operator opt-in via a `state.json.modes.historyBackend` flip per DB-P2-Guide.md §6 (B-checklist + C-checklist), with N=10 consecutive count-reconcile PASSes required for B→C. The mux exists so mode swap is invisible to callers (`append`/`query`/`exportJsonl`/`count` keep the same signature across all modes). JSONL is the **rollback floor** — in mode B it's canonical for reads (SQLite is shadow-only); in mode C it's regenerable byte-identically from SQLite. Backend driver is chosen ONCE per process startup via `selectSqliteBackend()` probe (`node:sqlite` primary on Node ≥22.5 + `--experimental-sqlite`; `better-sqlite3` fallback) and never re-evaluated per-write — determinism is load-bearing (a write that goes to `node:sqlite` and a subsequent write that goes to `better-sqlite3` would silently corrupt dual-write invariants). Failure modes (probe-failure / WAL corruption / partial-dual-write / count drift) surface as `BlockerManifest` per Constellation.md §13.20 — never silent. (Distilled from main upstream `history-store.cjs` per Delegate seq 159 / msgId m-mpu9febn-158 line-range mapping + EG DB-P2-Guide.md v2.4.3 commit `4bde4de`.)
@expansion temperature=0.2 model=agent/claude template=estreux/v0.0.1
@targets node
@profile backend-service
@state
# mode + probe
currentMode      : string = "jsonl"     # mode A jsonl | mode B dual | mode C sqlite (sourced from state.json.modes.historyBackend)
probeResult      : {kind,driver}|null = null   # selectSqliteBackend() cached result — set once at boot, never re-evaluated per-write
# auto-revert counters (per DB-P2-Guide §7.3 / §7.4)
driftCount       : number = 0           # count-reconcile FAIL count (window 30min); ≥2 → auto-revert mode A
partialFailCount : number = 0           # partial-dual-write failure count (window 10min); ≥3 → auto-revert mode A
# per-store internals
jsonlChans       : Map<chanKey,{events,bufQueue,saveTimer}>   # JsonlStore: in-memory ring per channel + debounced write buffer
sqliteDb         : Database|null = null  # SqliteStore: opened in mode B/C; null in mode A
HIST_DIR         : string                # ws-history/ root (active jsonl) — JsonlStore backing dir
ARCHIVED_DIR     : string                # ws-history/archived/ — ✕ closed channels (excluded from active scan)
SQLITE_PATH      : string                # <HIST_DIR>/history.db (only opened in mode B/C)
@ports
in   dir              : string          # HIST_DIR root (passed by server boot)
in   mode             : string          # initial mode from state.json.modes.historyBackend (jsonl|dual|sqlite)
in   onBlocker        : function?       # callback invoked on probe-failure / partial-fail / drift / promotion-blocked — payload is a BlockerManifest-shaped object (subject/reason/eg_side_action_waiting/tier)
cmd  createHistoryStore(opts) : HistoryStore  # entry point — returns a HistoryStoreMux that internally holds {JsonlStore, optional SqliteStore} per mode (L572-577)
cmd  append(ev) : void                  # route by currentMode — A→JsonlStore · B→JsonlStore + SqliteStore (dual, logical transaction) · C→SqliteStore primary (L508-521)
cmd  query(filter) : event[]            # mode A/B → JsonlStore (canonical for reads in mode B too); mode C → SqliteStore (L525-529 / Jsonl L92-102 / Sqlite L356-368)
cmd  exportJsonl() : Readable           # byte-identical JSONL stream (safety net, any mode) — Sqlite path reconstructs from rows preserving ts-then-id order per DB-P2-Guide §9.1 (L105-111 jsonl · L371-376 sqlite)
cmd  count() : number                   # JsonlStore.count (L114) · SqliteStore.count (L379); mux returns per-mode authoritative count (L525-529)
cmd  closeChannel(key) : void           # rename active .jsonl → cold stub {key,count,lastTs}; drop in-memory ring (L118-123)
cmd  deleteChannel(key) : void          # remove active + archived files for key (L131-137)
cmd  deleteAll() : void                 # wipe ws-history/ (active + archived) — operator destructive op (L139-146)
cmd  historyPayload() : {events,cold,archived}  # connect-time History envelope: active events flat array + cold stubs + archived stubs (L157-166)
cmd  loadChannel(key) : event[]         # RequestChannelHistory — load cold or archived back into active ring (L92-102 + restoration from archived/)
cmd  archiveChannel(key) : void         # move active .jsonl → archived/ (excluded from active scan/cap)
cmd  boot() : void                      # JsonlStore.boot rebuild from ws-history/ (re-key by event content via msgChan); SqliteStore.boot opens db + applies SQLITE_SCHEMA; mux composes both per mode (L214 jsonl · L492-505 mux)
cmd  reconcile() : {pass,jsonlCount,sqliteCount,diff}  # mode-B parity check — periodic (every ~10min OR 100 events) AND pre-C-promotion (N=10 consecutive PASSes per DB-P2-Guide §6.3) (L401-418 sqlite · L532-537 mux)
cmd  close() : void                     # graceful shutdown — flush jsonl write buffers, sqlite WAL TRUNCATE checkpoint, close db (L468)
out  BlockerManifest events             : via `onBlocker` callback — emitted on (a) `node:sqlite`+`better-sqlite3` both unavailable in mode B/C (refuse-to-start) · (b) WAL corruption (auto-rollback mode A) · (c) ≥3 partial-dual-write failures within 10min (`_recordPartialFail` L538-541 → `_autoRevert` L546-550) · (d) ≥2 count drifts within 30min (`_recordDrift` L542-545 → `_autoRevert` L546-550) · (e) mode-C promotion blocked (count-reconcile FAIL) — payload shape per Constellation.md §13.20 (`_emitBlocker` L551-553)
deps node:sqlite      : Node ≥22.5 builtin (primary backend) — probed first; requires `--experimental-sqlite` flag (L246-279)
deps better-sqlite3   : npm package (fallback backend) — probed if node:sqlite unavailable; mature synchronous SQLite driver (L246-279)
deps fs               : JSONL backing store IO — append+fsync per line; debounced write buffer 1s/channel; archived/ subdir IO (L41-52, L60-63, L75-88, L139-146)
deps HistoryStore     : abstract contract — append/query/exportJsonl/count/close (L26-34) — implemented by JsonlStore + SqliteStore + composed by HistoryStoreMux
@machine HistoryStoreMode
# reducer: (currentMode, event) → currentMode. The mode chain is strict opt-in (A → B → C); rollback is auto on gate failure OR operator manual.
states: A(initial, jsonl-only floor) · B(dual-write + backfill, transitional) · C(db-primary, terminal opt-in)
dispatch by event:
  arm                  : * → A                  (entry: fresh install or no state.json — JsonlStore only; SqliteStore + HistoryStoreMux dormant; no driver init)
  operator_flip_B      : A → B                  (guard: §6.2 B-checklist passes — backend probe succeeds OR better-sqlite3 npm-installed AND disk space available AND JSONL backup exists AND zero-traffic window; entry: open SqliteStore + apply SQLITE_SCHEMA + one-shot backfill from JSONL via `backfillFromJsonl` L383-398, INSERT OR IGNORE batched 500; post-check count reconcile must PASS)
  operator_flip_C      : B → C                  (guard: §6.3 C-checklist — N=10 consecutive count-reconcile PASSes AND zero read-path errors ≥1 cycle AND exportJsonl round-trip verified AND zero-traffic window; entry: stop inline JSONL writes; SqliteStore becomes canonical for reads + writes)
  count_drift_2_in_30m : B → A                  (entry: `_recordDrift` accumulates → `_autoRevert`; flip currentMode in-memory ONLY (do NOT mutate state.json — preserve operator intent across restarts); emit BlockerManifest tier 2-explicit per §7.4)
  partial_fail_3_in_10m: B → A                  (entry: `_recordPartialFail` → `_autoRevert`; same in-memory revert + BlockerManifest as count drift; per §7.3)
  wal_corruption       : B|C → A                (entry: operator manual flip state.json modes.historyBackend=jsonl; preserve corrupted .db as `sqlite-corrupted-<ts>.db` for forensic review; per §7.2)
  operator_rollback_C_B: C → B                  (entry: replay SQLite → JSONL via `exportJsonl` to bring JSONL current; resume dual-writes; per §2.3 rollback path)
  operator_rollback_C_A: C → A                  (entry: one-shot exportJsonl materializes canonical JSONL; stop SQLite writes; per §2.3 rollback path — JSONL is the floor)
  probe_fail_modeBC    : B|C startup → ⊗        (guard: both node:sqlite AND better-sqlite3 unavailable; entry: refuse to start, exit non-zero, emit BlockerManifest — DO NOT silently degrade to mode A because operator intent (state.json) was SQLite; per §3.3 / §7.1)
guard:
  mode-B-backfill-complete-and-count-pass  : SqliteStore.count() == JsonlStore.count() AFTER `backfillFromJsonl` completes (one-shot INSERT OR IGNORE batched 500 per §4.4); FAIL → abort B promotion + revert state.json + emit BlockerManifest per §4.2 post-check
  mode-C-zero-traffic-gate                 : §6.3 — pendingDeliveries == 0 AND N=10 consecutive reconcile PASSes AND zero read-path errors ≥24h AND exportJsonl round-trip byte-identical; one fail blocks promotion (operator must re-verify) per §2.4 + §6.3
@source history-store.cjs(L26-34) HistoryStore abstract contract: append/query/exportJsonl/count/close — the surface every store implements + the mux composes
@source history-store.cjs(L39-215) JsonlStore — constructor L41-52 (dir + per-channel state init) · msgChan L55 (route event → channel key by content, not filename) · _saveChan L60-63 (debounced 1s/channel write) · _store L65-72 (push to in-memory ring + buffer) · append L75-88 (atomic append: open+write+fsync+close; ring cap 200; streaming compression on _START→buffer / _CONTENT→accumulate / _END→store-1) · query L92-102 · exportJsonl L105-111 · count L114 · closeChannel L118-123 (active→cold stub) · deleteChannel L131-137 · deleteAll L139-146 · historyPayload L157-166 (connect-time {events,cold,archived}) · loadAll L187-201 (boot rebuild — re-key by content via msgChan, normalize ts, sort, cap; drop orphans) · migrate L203-211 (legacy ws-history.json → per-channel split + .bak) · boot L214
@source history-store.cjs(L225-238) SQLITE_SCHEMA — `events` table DDL (id PK · thread_id · agent_id · ts · name · value_json · source) + three indexes (idx_events_thread_ts · idx_events_agent_ts · idx_events_ts) mirroring DB-P2-Guide §8; INSERT OR IGNORE on `id` PK is the backfill idempotency key
@source history-store.cjs(L246-279) selectSqliteBackend — startup probe: (1) Node ≥22.5 semver check · (2) `--experimental-sqlite` flag check in process.execArgv / NODE_OPTIONS · (3) `require('node:sqlite')` try · (4) `require('better-sqlite3')` fallback try · (5) refuse to start in mode B/C if neither available; cached in `probeResult`, never re-evaluated per-write
@source history-store.cjs(L286-469) SqliteStore — constructor L288-307 · _openDb L309-323 (open db + PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL + apply SQLITE_SCHEMA) · _eventId L331-335 (mirror JSONL event id; do NOT regenerate on insert) · _cols L336-345 (extract thread_id/agent_id/ts/name from value_json for denormalized indexed reads) · append L352 (INSERT OR IGNORE — transaction wraps; JSONL append is the "decision point", SQLite COMMIT is the "commit point" per DB-P2-Guide §7.3 logical transaction discipline) · query L356-368 · exportJsonl L371-376 (reconstruct ordered byte-identical JSONL per §9.1: ORDER BY ts ASC, id ASC) · count L379 · backfillFromJsonl L383-398 (one-shot mode-B entry: stream JSONL line-by-line, batch 500, INSERT OR IGNORE — idempotent, resume-safe per §4.3) · reconcile L401-418 (count + discrepancy report {only_in_jsonl,only_in_sqlite} per §5.3) · close L468 (WAL TRUNCATE checkpoint + db.close)
@source history-store.cjs(L475-567) HistoryStoreMux — constructor L477-489 (composes JsonlStore + optional SqliteStore per mode; holds onBlocker callback + drift/partial-fail counters) · boot L492-505 (boot both stores; SqliteStore only opened in mode B/C) · append L508-521 (route by currentMode: A→jsonl · B→dual-write logical transaction · C→sqlite primary) · query/count/exportJsonl L525-529 (mode-routed; mode B reads from jsonl canonical) · reconcile L532-537 (delegate to SqliteStore.reconcile; record outcome) · _recordPartialFail L538-541 (sliding 10min window; ≥3 → _autoRevert) · _recordDrift L542-545 (sliding 30min window; ≥2 → _autoRevert) · _autoRevert L546-550 (in-memory mode A; do NOT mutate state.json — operator intent preserved across restarts per §7.4) · _emitBlocker L551-553 (invoke onBlocker with §13.20-shaped payload)
@source history-store.cjs(L572-577) createHistoryStore — entry point factory: takes {dir, mode, onBlocker}; calls selectSqliteBackend once; returns HistoryStoreMux instance to server.cjs as the single opaque `historyStore` handle
@behavior
appendRouting    : append(ev) routes by currentMode (L508-521). **mode A** — JsonlStore only (`_store` ring + `_saveChan` debounced 1s write); SqliteStore is null. **mode B** — logical transaction: (1) BEGIN sqlite tx (2) JsonlStore.append → success is the decision point (3) SqliteStore INSERT OR IGNORE (4) COMMIT sqlite. On either throw: if JSONL succeeded + SQLite failed → `ftruncate(2)` to previous offset to undo the JSONL append (JSONL is line-oriented so single syscall); if SQLite succeeded + JSONL failed → ROLLBACK the SQLite tx. Either path → `_recordPartialFail` (sliding 10min window). **mode C** — SqliteStore primary; no inline JSONL write (JSONL regenerable via `exportJsonl` only). Per DB-P2-Guide §7.3.
backfillEntry    : on operator A→B flip, mux.boot opens SqliteStore + applies SQLITE_SCHEMA. Pre-check `SqliteStore.count()`: if 0 run full backfill (`backfillFromJsonl` L383-398); if >0 and < `JsonlStore.count()` run partial backfill (resume from max(id) — INSERT OR IGNORE makes this safe); if ≥ skip backfill + immediate count-reconcile. Backfill streams JSONL line-by-line, batches into chunks of 500, wraps each chunk in a transaction, INSERT OR IGNORE by event id. Post-check count-reconcile (§5) — PASS activates mode B; FAIL reverts state.json modes.historyBackend=jsonl + emits BlockerManifest. Idempotent (re-running safe). Per §4.
reconcileCadence : mode-B periodic check every ~10min OR every ~100 new events (whichever first). Pre-mode-C promotion requires N=10 consecutive PASSes (per §6.3 — rationale: balances detection-sensitivity vs operator wait time ≈100min of clean parity; main may tune upward but not below 10). Single FAIL → `_recordDrift` (sliding 30min window) + generate discrepancy report {ts,jsonl_count,sqlite_count,only_in_jsonl,only_in_sqlite,investigation_hint}; surface as BlockerManifest subject=operator + tier 2-explicit. Do NOT auto-resolve drift (operator review forces understanding *why* the drift occurred). Per §5.3.
autoRevert       : `_autoRevert` triggers on (drift count ≥2 within 30min) OR (partial-fail count ≥3 within 10min). Effect: flip `currentMode = "jsonl"` **in-memory only** (do NOT mutate state.json — operator's recorded intent must survive a restart so they see the rollback decision when next they boot). Subsequent appends go only to JsonlStore. Emit BlockerManifest tier 2-explicit with subject=operator, reason=parity failure / partial-write failure, eg_side_action_waiting=operator decision {re-enter mode B (re-run backfill) | persist mode A (set state.json modes.historyBackend=jsonl) | investigate discrepancy report}. Per §7.3 + §7.4.
exportJsonlSafetyNet : `exportJsonl()` MUST produce byte-identical output to canonical JSONL within §9.1 tolerances — ORDER BY ts ASC, id ASC; deterministic field-order within each JSON event matching the original JSONL writer; trailing newline at EOF matches. Available in ANY mode (mode A: trivially echoes JSONL; mode B: reconstructs from SqliteStore (verified vs canonical JSONL via diff during mode-B operation per §6.3 / §9.3); mode C: the ONLY way to rebuild JSONL — this is the rollback floor for mode C). Per §9.
walCorruption    : symptoms (`database disk image is malformed` errors / checksum failures on WAL replay / unexpected NULLs). Recovery (operator-driven, NOT auto): (1) state.json.modes.historyBackend = "jsonl" (2) restart server (mode-A startup; SQLite not loaded) (3) verify JSONL healthy (4) preserve corrupted .db as `sqlite-corrupted-<ts>.db` for forensic review (do NOT delete — evidence) (5) optional retry: re-enter mode B per §6.2; backfill from JSONL recreates the .db from scratch. JSONL is the rollback floor — WAL corruption never threatens canonical data in mode A or B; only mode C relies on `exportJsonl()` as the safety net. Per §7.2.
probeRefusal     : if mode B or mode C is selected at startup AND both `node:sqlite` and `better-sqlite3` are unavailable → refuse to start (throw, exit non-zero), emit BlockerManifest. Do NOT silently degrade to mode A — operator intent (state.json) was SQLite; silent degradation hides the failure. Per §3.3 + §7.1.
@rationale Independent backend track — JSONL stays the floor / safety net so rollback is always free at any mode. SQLite is opt-in (operator state.json flip), never auto-enabled. The mux exists so a mode swap is invisible to callers — every consumer of `historyStore.append/query/exportJsonl/count` keeps the same signature across all three modes; only the routing inside the mux changes. Separation from `server.cjs` (factored into `history-store.cjs` ~580 lines) isolates the migration discipline so server-side relay/record paths in `server.cjs` continue to call a single opaque `historyStore` handle returned by `createHistoryStore(opts)` — no per-mode branching leaks into the WS lifecycle. The `_autoRevert` keeps the server *running* in a known-good state while surfacing the failure for operator review — graceful degradation, never silent degradation. The N=10 consecutive PASSes gate for B→C promotion is deliberately conservative (≈100min at 10min cadence): the count-reconcile gate exists *because* dual-write atomicity is not perfect (race conditions, crash recovery, transaction-abort timing) — auto-resolving drift would mask the underlying defect.
@hazards
# C7 — DB integrity surfaces per eux-format v1.1 §2.5 @hazards (DB 무결성 한정) — added phase_2 2026-06-04
db_integrity_surfaces:
  - sqlite_db_file: ws-history.db (mode B/C only — gitignored, NEVER commit; carries channel history bytes)
  - wal_journal: ws-history.db-wal (WAL mode write-ahead log; crash recovery depends on WAL replay integrity)
  - jsonl_rollback_floor: per-channel .jsonl files (canonical in mode A, shadow in mode B, regenerable in mode C via exportJsonl)
  - operator_state: state.json.modes.historyBackend (operator intent — A/B/C; survives restart; never auto-mutate on failure)
integrity_invariants:
  dual_write_atomicity_mode_b: appendRouting MUST roll back the side that succeeded if the other side fails — JSONL ftruncate(2) to previous offset (line-oriented single syscall) OR SQLite ROLLBACK tx. Partial-fail tracked in 10min sliding window for auto-revert trigger.
  count_reconcile_gate: mode-B periodic JsonlStore.count() == SqliteStore.count() ≥ 10 consecutive PASSes required for B→C promotion (per §6.3 — operator may tune upward, NEVER below 10)
  byte_identical_export: exportJsonl() MUST produce byte-identical JSONL within §9.1 tolerances (ORDER BY ts ASC, id ASC; deterministic field-order; trailing newline) — this is the rollback floor for mode C
  backfill_idempotency: backfillFromJsonl uses INSERT OR IGNORE by event id; re-running is safe (no duplication, no skip on partial completion)
  probe_determinism: selectSqliteBackend() runs ONCE per process startup; never re-evaluated per-write (would silently corrupt dual-write invariants if backend switched mid-process)
  jsonl_rollback_floor_never_violated: JSONL is canonical-or-regenerable in EVERY mode — WAL corruption / SQLite probe failure / partial-write never threatens canonical data integrity at JSONL layer
threat_model:
  silent_silent_degradation: operator selects mode B/C → both SQLite drivers unavailable → silent fallback to mode A would mask operator intent (mitigated by probeRefusal — throw + BlockerManifest, exit non-zero)
  wal_corruption_undetected: WAL replay produces NULL/corrupted data → mode C reads corrupted bytes silently (mitigated by walCorruption recovery operator-driven path — preserve .db as evidence + rebuild via mode-B backfill)
  drift_auto_resolution: auto-resolving drift between JsonlStore and SqliteStore would mask the underlying defect (atomicity bug / race condition / crash timing) — operator review forces understanding *why* (per §5.3 enforced design)
  state_json_intent_mutation: auto-reverting state.json.modes.historyBackend on failure would erase operator's recorded intent — operator's intent must survive restart so they see the rollback decision when next they boot (mitigated by autoRevert in-memory only, NEVER mutate state.json on failure)
  exportJsonl_drift_silent: byte-non-identical exportJsonl output in mode B/C would mean rollback floor is corrupted (mitigated by §9.3 periodic diff verification during mode-B operation)
recovery_discipline:
  walCorruption: operator-driven 5-step recovery (state.json flip A → restart → verify JSONL → preserve corrupted .db as forensic evidence → optional retry B backfill); JSONL rollback floor never threatened in mode A or B
  partial_dual_write_failure: sliding 10min window count ≥ 3 → autoRevert in-memory (mode A) + BlockerManifest tier 2-explicit + operator decision required
  drift_detection: single FAIL → discrepancy report {jsonl_count, sqlite_count, only_in_jsonl, only_in_sqlite, investigation_hint} + BlockerManifest; sliding 30min ≥ 2 drift FAILs → autoRevert
@invariants
  # P3 AST 계약스키마 — phase_3 1st cut per eux-format v1.2 §2.6 (EstreUX 884552b). prose+vocabulary 형식 (Q1=c).
  state:
    - jsonlChans 채널별 events 는 HIST_CAP=200 으로 bounded
    - wsHistByChan events 는 timestamp ASC ordered + INSERT OR IGNORE 로 id monotonic 증가 (never overwrite)
    - currentMode 는 {jsonl, dual, sqlite} member-of (operator intent 가 state.json 에 persist)
    - jsonl_rollback_floor: 모든 mode 에서 JSONL 이 canonical 또는 regenerable — wal_corruption / sqlite probe failure / partial-write 가 canonical data 위협 X (무결성 monotonic preservation)
  temporal:
    - selectSqliteBackend() 는 process 시작 시 at-most-once 호출, 결과 process 종료까지 expires-after (never re-evaluated per-write)
    - _recordDrift 는 30min sliding window 내 ≥2 FAIL within 시 _autoRevert trigger
    - _recordPartialFail 은 10min sliding window 내 ≥3 FAIL within 시 _autoRevert trigger
    - mode-B reconcile cadence: 10min after OR 100 events after, 둘 중 먼저 (cadence trigger)
    - boot 후 wsLoadAll 는 idempotent (재기동 시 동일 endstate; disk state 가 canonical)
  transaction:
    - mode B append 는 jsonlStore + sqliteStore dual-write atomic — 한쪽 실패 시 다른 쪽 rollback-safe (ftruncate JSONL OR ROLLBACK sqlite tx)
    - backfillFromJsonl 는 INSERT OR IGNORE 로 idempotent — 1회/N회 실행 결과 동일
    - exportJsonl 는 byte-identical (ORDER BY ts ASC, id ASC) — mode A trivial · mode B verified · mode C 의 rollback floor (commit-then byte 결과)
    - autoRevert 는 currentMode in-memory 만 변경, state.json mutation 금지 (operator intent persist-before 자동 변경 차단 metadata)
    - probeRefusal: mode B/C 선택 + 양 driver 미가용 시 refuse-to-start (atomic startup, silent degradation 금지)
  causality:
    - operator intent (state.json modes.historyBackend) precedes auto-revert decision (intent 가 restart 후 surface)
    - backfill_complete iff count-reconcile.pass — 둘 다 성공 시 mode B promotion 가능
    - WAL corruption recovery implies operator-driven 5-step path (auto recovery 금지 by design)
@metamorphic
  # P4 property/metamorphic 후보 — phase_3 1st cut per eux-format v1.2 §2.7 (EstreUX 884552b). round-trip/idempotency/determinism.
  round_trip:
    - mode-B exportJsonl → fresh JSONL → mode-B 재진입 + backfillFromJsonl → exportJsonl 결과 byte-identical (전체 cycle 동일성)
    - active → cold (agent_present_lost) → active (RequestChannelHistory): events 동일 (lifecycle preservation)
    - active → archived (explicit close) → active (RequestChannelHistory): events 동일 (archive round-trip)
  idempotency:
    - backfillFromJsonl 1회 vs N회 실행 결과 동일 (INSERT OR IGNORE 보장)
    - record(ev) 의 skip set 내 event (HELLO/Heartbeat 등) 는 0회 또는 N회 동일 endstate
  determinism:
    - 동일 ev 입력 시 jsonlStore + sqliteStore append 결과 deterministic (probe once + driver fixed per-process)
    - exportJsonl ordering (ts ASC, id ASC) 결과 deterministic across mode B verification cycles
@incident seq 79 DB RRP (`m-mpt4mzo9-78`, 2026-05-31) — originating agreement that fixed the three-mode shape: P1 (HistoryStore abstraction + JsonlStore) → P2 (dual-write + backfill + SqliteStore) → P3 (db-primary). Mode-letter naming (A/B/C) is this guide's convenience handle on top of the seq 79 chain; the chain itself unchanged. · seq 144 (`m-mptlrmm3-143`, 2026-05-31) — DB P2 ship trigger Delegate from main upstream requesting EG-side P2 guide; satisfied by `constellation/reference/docs/DB-P2-Guide.md` v0.1. · seq 155 — main upstream commit `a28150e` DB P2 ship + EG DB-P2-Guide.md v2.4.3 정합 (history-store.cjs factored out of server.cjs, ~580 lines, separate file). · seq 159 (`m-mpu9febn-158`) — a5bc §F line-range mapping used to author this .eux's @source ranges (JsonlStore L39-215 · SQLITE_SCHEMA L225-238 · selectSqliteBackend L246-279 · SqliteStore L286-469 · HistoryStoreMux L475-567 · createHistoryStore L572-577).
